## 3. Quality Gates (ALL must pass before `kanban_complete` on your planning task)

```
GATE 1 — {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} Anchoring
☐ Every card created references a {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} story id in its title (e.g. "T-006: redaction scanner")
☐ Every card body links the {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} section it derives from (e.g. "{{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} §3 Epic 1.4")

GATE 2 — AC / DoD Completeness
☐ Every card has Acceptance Criteria in Given/When/Then format (minimum 3 criteria)
☐ Every card has a Definition of Done checklist
☐ Each AC is testable — no "it should work" or "it should be reliable" hand-waving
☐ Each DoD item is verifiable by {{ project.slug }}-qa via test or inspection

GATE 3 — Dependencies
☐ Dependencies expressed via parents=[...], NOT prose in the body ("wait for T-N" is forbidden)
☐ Parent cards exist (you create them in order, capture their returned task_ids, use those ids in children)
☐ No phantom dependencies — every parent referenced must actually be required input

GATE 4 — Phase Discipline
☐ Cards respect {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} phase ordering (P1 cards before P2, etc.)
☐ Phase gates from {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} (the "Phase N Acceptance Gate" sections) are encoded as parent chains
☐ Phase 1 redaction story (T-006) is a parent of Phase 1 capture (T-007) per critical ordering

GATE 5 — Risk Awareness
☐ High-severity issues from docs/v0.2-critique.md are reflected in card AC where relevant
    - Issue 1 (narrative-thread injection) — covered in Phase 5 stories
    - Issue 2 (SQLite concurrency) — Phase 1 schema story includes writer-ownership decision
    - Issue 3 (indexer process model) — Phase 3 indexer story includes catch-up-on-init
☐ ADRs ({{ paths.adr_root | default("docs/adr/") }}*.md) are referenced where they cover the story

GATE 6 — Sizing
☐ Card size matches {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} story size (XS/S/M/L/XL)
☐ No M+ cards created without size in the body

GATE 7 — Single-Lane Discipline
☐ Each card is one focused workstream
☐ "Implement X AND document Y" is two cards (one to {{ project.slug }}-developer, one to {{ project.slug }}-docs with parent=[dev_card])
```

**If ANY gate fails:** Fix the cards before completing your own task. Recreate or update via `kanban_update` if necessary.

