## 5. Decomposition Playbook (per sprint)

Standard sprint = "land Phase N of {{ project.dir_name | default(project.slug) }}."

### Step 1 — Read

- Read {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} §<phase> end-to-end
- Read {{ inputs.epics_md | default("EPICS.md") }} Phase N section
- Read v0.2-critique.md for any items tagged that phase
- Read any ADRs in {{ paths.adr_root | default("docs/adr/") }} that touch this phase

### Step 2 — Identify cards

{{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} already enumerates stories (e.g. Phase 1: T-001..T-010). Each {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} story = one kanban card. Don't add cards {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} doesn't describe. Don't drop cards {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} does describe.

### Step 3 — Determine dependencies

- Phase ordering enforced by parent links (Phase 2 cards have a `phase1-gate` parent — see §6)
- Within-phase ordering called out in {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} (e.g. "T-006 redaction BEFORE T-007 capture")
- Encode every "BEFORE" / "must precede" as `parents=[earlier_task_id]`

### Step 4 — Assign

Mapping from story type → profile:

| Story type | Assignee |
|---|---|
| Plan / decompose / triage | {{ project.slug }}-planner |
| Tech spec, ADR, schema design | {{ project.slug }}-architect |
| Code, tests, refactor | {{ project.slug }}-developer |
| Verify / approve / reject | {{ project.slug }}-qa |
| Update PROJECT/TASKLIST/EPICS docs | {{ project.slug }}-docs |

### Step 5 — Create in order

```python
import os
TENANT = os.environ.get("HERMES_TENANT")

# Phase 1, P1, no parents
t_001 = kanban_create(
    title="T-001: scaffold plugin + memory_core skeleton",
    assignee="{{ project.slug }}-developer",
    body=<template per §4>,
    tenant=TENANT,
)["task_id"]

# T-006 redaction must precede T-007 capture
t_006 = kanban_create(
    title="T-006: redaction scanner",
    assignee="{{ project.slug }}-developer",
    body=<template>,
    tenant=TENANT,
)["task_id"]

t_007 = kanban_create(
    title="T-007: capture pipeline (uses redaction)",
    assignee="{{ project.slug }}-developer",
    parents=[t_006],
    body=<template>,
    tenant=TENANT,
)["task_id"]

# Each developer card also gets a downstream qa card
t_007_qa = kanban_create(
    title="T-007-qa: verify capture pipeline",
    assignee="{{ project.slug }}-qa",
    parents=[t_007],
    body=<template>,
    tenant=TENANT,
)["task_id"]
```

### Step 6 — Phase gate

Optional but recommended: create a single `phase-N-gate` card assigned to {{ project.slug }}-qa that has ALL of the phase's qa cards as parents. When that gate card is `done`, the phase is officially complete. Phase N+1 cards have it as a parent.

```python
phase1_gate = kanban_create(
    title="T-PHASE1-GATE: Phase 1 acceptance scenarios A+B (capture+redaction)",
    assignee="{{ project.slug }}-qa",
    parents=[t_001_qa, t_002_qa, ..., t_010_qa],
    body="Runs {{ inputs.plan_md | default('Plan.md') }} {{ phases.acceptance_test_section | default('§9') }} Scenarios A and B. Approve only if both pass.",
    tenant=TENANT,
)
```

### Step 7 — Report

In your `kanban_complete` summary:

```markdown
## Decomposition complete — Phase N

### Cards created (N total)
- T-001 ({{ project.slug }}-developer): scaffold plugin
- T-006 ({{ project.slug }}-developer): redaction scanner
- T-007 ({{ project.slug }}-developer, parents=[T-006]): capture pipeline
- ... (full list)

### Dependency graph
- T-006 → T-007 → T-007-qa → T-PHASE1-GATE
- T-001 → ...

### Notes
- High-severity critique items addressed: <list>
- Anything that was AMBIGUOUS or worth flagging to the human
```

