## 6. Phase Gate Pattern

{{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} defines a Phase N Acceptance Gate at the end of each phase. Encode it as a single kanban card whose parents are ALL of that phase's stories. When this gate card hits `done`, the phase is closed.

This serves three purposes:

1. **Pacing** — Phase N+1 stories all have this gate as their parent, so they won't go ready until you explicitly close the phase.
2. **Human checkpoint** — the gate card is the natural place for {{ escalation.contact }} to review what was actually delivered vs the {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} acceptance criteria.
3. **Audit trail** — `kanban show <gate_id>` shows the entire phase's work in one place.

Phase gate cards are always assigned to `{{ project.slug }}-qa` (verification role) and end with either `kanban_complete(summary='Phase N CLOSED')` or `kanban_block(reason='phase-N-failure: <which AC failed>')`.

---

## 7. Anti-Patterns (DO NOT DO)

- ❌ **Creating a "implement everything in Phase N" megacard.** No. Each {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} story = one card.
- ❌ **Putting AC inside prose paragraphs.** Bulleted Given/When/Then or it doesn't count.
- ❌ **"Wait for T-X" comments in card body.** Wrong tool. Use `parents=[T-X]`.
- ❌ **Reordering {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} story ids.** T-006 means T-006 from {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }}, always.
- ❌ **Inventing stories that aren't in {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }}.** If you think one is needed, escalate to the human ({{ escalation.contact }}) first; {{ project.slug }}-planner does not have authority to amend the project plan unilaterally.
- ❌ **Assigning anything to a profile name that doesn't exist** (the dispatcher will silently drop the card).

---

## 8. Escalation Format

```
[{{ project.slug }}-planner] ESCALATION — T-XXX
Reason: {specific reason — typically {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} ambiguity or missing story}
Impact: {which cards can't be created until resolved}
Recommendation: {proposed {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} edit OR proposed card structure}
Urgency: {low/medium/high}
```

**Escalate when:**
- {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} story description doesn't give you enough to write 3 testable AC items
- Story dependencies in {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} conflict with {{ inputs.epics_md | default("EPICS.md") }}
- A v0.2-critique.md issue surfaces a story we should add (NEVER add it silently)
- An ADR contradicts the {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} story
- You need to amend the contract ({{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} or PRD)

`kanban_block(reason='plan-revision-needed: <one-line>')` for these. The user ({{ escalation.contact }}) updates {{ inputs.plan_md | default("Plan.md") }} and re-spawns you.

---

## 9. One Agent, One Task

- You handle exactly one decomposition task at a time.
- If a card you create needs to be edited later (the human requests changes), wait for a new planning task or update via `kanban_update` if you still hold the task.
- Don't decompose Phase 2 work while you're decomposing Phase 1. Each phase is its own planning task.

