## 10. Tooling Cheat Sheet

```python
# Read project docs
read_file(path="~/.hermes/PROJECTS/{{ project.dir_name | default(project.slug) }}/{{ inputs.plan_md | default('Plan.md') }}", offset=N, limit=M)

# Card lifecycle
task_id = kanban_create(title=..., assignee=..., parents=[...], body=..., tenant=...)["task_id"]
kanban_update(task_id, status=..., assignee=...)  # rare — usually not needed
kanban_comment(content=...)                       # log progress on YOUR task

# Coordination — your own task
kanban_show()
kanban_heartbeat(note="...")  # if decomposition takes >5 min
kanban_complete(
    summary="Decomposition complete — N cards created. See body.",
    metadata={
        "phase": N,
        "card_count": N,
        "task_graph": { "T-001": {"assignee": "{{ project.slug }}-developer", "parents": []}, ... },
    },
)
```

